    <exercise id="fs-id3259487" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id3259490">

    <para id="import-auto-id2453093">Define the quantum numbers <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">n, l,</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mi fontstyle="italic">, s</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>s</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m rSub { size 8{s} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para></problem></exercise>
        <exercise id="fs-id1859624" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id1859626">

    <para id="import-auto-id3417998">For a given value of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{n} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, what are the allowed values of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{l} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>?</para>
    </problem></exercise>
        <exercise id="fs-id3033126" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id2017403">

    <para id="import-auto-id2683190">For a given value of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{l} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, what are the allowed values of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m rSub { size 8{l} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>? What are the allowed values of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m rSub { size 8{l} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> for a given value of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{n} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>? Give an example in each case.</para>
